{"pageProps":{"post":{"creator":"Marc Reid","title":"Tableau Image Role + Cloudinary","link":"https://datavis.blog/2023/01/23/tableau-image-role-and-cloudinary/","pubDate":"Mon, 23 Jan 2023 18:10:12 +0000","content:encoded":"\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is an Image Role?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For some years now, it’s been possible to assign a <strong>Geographic Role</strong> to a field in your data, such as an Airport, City, or Zip Code:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3403\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2023/01/23/tableau-image-role-and-cloudinary/tableau-geographic-role-menu/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-geographic-role-menu.png\" data-orig-size=\"357,447\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"tableau-geographic-role-menu\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-geographic-role-menu.png?w=240\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-geographic-role-menu.png?w=357\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-geographic-role-menu.png?w=357\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3403\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-geographic-role-menu.png 357w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-geographic-role-menu.png?w=120 120w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-geographic-role-menu.png?w=240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 357px) 100vw, 357px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>In version 2022.4, Tableau introduced the new <strong>Image Role</strong>, which can be assigned to a string field that contains a URL for an image:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3404\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2023/01/23/tableau-image-role-and-cloudinary/tableau-image-role-menu/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-image-role-menu.png\" data-orig-size=\"246,271\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"tableau-image-role-menu\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-image-role-menu.png?w=246\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-image-role-menu.png?w=246\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-image-role-menu.png?w=246\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3404\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-image-role-menu.png 246w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/tableau-image-role-menu.png?w=136 136w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 246px) 100vw, 246px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>Note the distinction between <strong>data type</strong> and<strong> role</strong>. Data types are mandatory and are assigned in the top half of the menu above (Number, String etc.); <strong>Geographic and Image Roles are <em>additional</em> and <em>optional</em> properties of a field </strong>that instruct Tableau to treat those fields in a certain way.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When a string field that is assigned an image role is brought into the view as a header, <strong>instead of displaying the URL as text, Tableau will fetch the image and display that in its place.</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is Cloudinary?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of Cloudinary’s products is <strong>programmable media</strong>, which means it can dynamically deliver variations of images based on API calls or parameters in URLs. Have a look at their <a href=\"https://cloudinary.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">website</a> to learn more.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Image Role + Cloudinary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Combining Tableau’s image role feature with the ability to dynamically generate images based on URL strings with Cloudinary opens up some interesting possibilities and Tableau Visionary, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TableauTim\">Tim Ngwena</a>, explored these in this <a href=\"https://youtu.be/fSRzNi-_u5g\">in-depth video</a>, which I highly recommend. Inspired by Tim’s work, the following explores a possible use case.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Sales by Person &#8211; No Image</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We start with a standard bar graph, colour-coded &#8211; gold, silver, bronze (and no colour) &#8211; based on a sales figure.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3405\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2023/01/23/tableau-image-role-and-cloudinary/01-no-image/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/01-no-image.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"1000,711\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"01-no-image\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/01-no-image.jpg?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/01-no-image.jpg?w=736\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/01-no-image.jpg?w=1000\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3405\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/01-no-image.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/01-no-image.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/01-no-image.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/01-no-image.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Adding Image Role</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An image of each sales person is now shown in the header using a standard image role, with all images hosted on Cloudinary.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>(Note, the original images were sourced from <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://pixabay.com/\" target=\"_blank\">pixabay</a> and <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://unsplash.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Unsplash</a>)</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3406\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2023/01/23/tableau-image-role-and-cloudinary/02-image-no-edits/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"1000,711\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"02-image-no-edits\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=736\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=1000\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3406\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>Things we could improve:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>The images are different formats &#8211; portrait and landscape</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The images are not centred within each row due to the column width</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The different photo styles and backgrounds give an inconsistent look so don’t blend in well with the chart</li>\n\n\n\n<li>No analytical information is conveyed with the images</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Change the image by changing the URL</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>By changing parameters in the dashboard, we can update the URL, which will then result in a new image (with those specified adjustments) being returned.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, in the calculation below, if the user has specified they want to change the image dimensions (<strong>p.Change Dimensions = TRUE</strong>) then a string with those dimensions is returned, which is then added into the image URL (in a different calculation). If not, then an empty string is returned so the URL is not altered.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3407\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2023/01/23/tableau-image-role-and-cloudinary/width-height-calc/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/width-height-calc.png\" data-orig-size=\"672,179\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"width-height-calc\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/width-height-calc.png?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/width-height-calc.png?w=672\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/width-height-calc.png?w=672\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3407\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/width-height-calc.png 672w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/width-height-calc.png?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/width-height-calc.png?w=300 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 672px) 100vw, 672px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Six image iterations</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The following set of images make the following changes (click/tap the right arrow to see the next image):</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Resizes the images </strong>&#8211; this doesn’t really work as the images become distorted in this case</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Cropping the image </strong>&#8211; this makes all the images the same size and they fill the space, which is good, but we lose the subject</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Cropping to the face </strong>&#8211; using <strong>face detection</strong>, we can crop all the images to same dimension focussed on the face</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Circular shape </strong>&#8211; making the images circular gives them a more profile look</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Add a blue border </strong>&#8211; gives all the images a similar (and possibly branded/company) style</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stylise the images </strong>with a cartoon effect &#8211; I’ve seen similar with some company photos, again to give a common style</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow aligncenter\" data-effect=\"slide\"><div class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_container swiper-container\"><ul class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_swiper-wrapper swiper-wrapper\"><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide\"><figure><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-3408\" data-id=\"3408\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02b-resized-images.jpg?w=1000\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02b-resized-images.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02b-resized-images.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02b-resized-images.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02b-resized-images.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure></li><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide\"><figure><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-3409\" data-id=\"3409\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/03-centre-crop.jpg?w=1000\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/03-centre-crop.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/03-centre-crop.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/03-centre-crop.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/03-centre-crop.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure></li><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide\"><figure><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-3410\" data-id=\"3410\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/04-face-detection.jpg?w=1000\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/04-face-detection.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/04-face-detection.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/04-face-detection.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/04-face-detection.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure></li><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide\"><figure><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-3411\" data-id=\"3411\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/05-circle-shape.jpg?w=1000\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/05-circle-shape.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/05-circle-shape.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/05-circle-shape.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/05-circle-shape.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure></li><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide\"><figure><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-3412\" data-id=\"3412\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/06-blue-border.jpg?w=1000\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/06-blue-border.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/06-blue-border.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/06-blue-border.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/06-blue-border.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure></li><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide\"><figure><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-3413\" data-id=\"3413\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/07-stylised.jpg?w=1000\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/07-stylised.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/07-stylised.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/07-stylised.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/07-stylised.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure></li></ul><a class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_button-prev swiper-button-prev swiper-button-white\" role=\"button\"></a><a class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_button-next swiper-button-next swiper-button-white\" role=\"button\"></a><a aria-label=\"Pause Slideshow\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_button-pause\" role=\"button\"></a><div class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_pagination swiper-pagination swiper-pagination-white\"></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Make the images data-driven</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This is where things get a little more analytical. Instead of a fixed colour border for all images, what if we determined the colour based on the sales metric (or the sports score, or last month’s profit per item etc…)?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With a simple RANK() calculation, based on the sales measure, I was able to assign a dynamic border to each image based on sales in that month.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/8scbXxrXQnj6IBF4DnD17kCuVr0WvC-QaZNbUlKmHMehEqOJBumA_Q2nZDEw054yP1CjwUlD95aIfUB5khc3y6zoWMJRrZxAFyydQDYxAnT_4iXMIZEOPEEcGwNPdg_zJFVL22oAgwSTv6FEGADshJlwUIz25sh2BWRbnQFE99lZmgqSFMASfOOqc5njZw\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>Adding a filter month on the dashboard, we can then change the month and see the image borders update based on monthly sales to match the bar colour.&nbsp;Scroll through the images below for Jan, Feb, March:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow aligncenter\" data-effect=\"slide\"><div class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_container swiper-container\"><ul class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_swiper-wrapper swiper-wrapper\"><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide\"><figure><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-3415\" data-id=\"3415\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08-dynamic-feb-filter.jpg?w=1000\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08-dynamic-feb-filter.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08-dynamic-feb-filter.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08-dynamic-feb-filter.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08-dynamic-feb-filter.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure></li><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide\"><figure><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-3416\" data-id=\"3416\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan-filter.jpg?w=1000\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan-filter.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan-filter.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan-filter.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan-filter.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure></li><li class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_slide swiper-slide\"><figure><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_image wp-image-3417\" data-id=\"3417\" src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08c-dynamic-march-filter.jpg?w=1000\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08c-dynamic-march-filter.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08c-dynamic-march-filter.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08c-dynamic-march-filter.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08c-dynamic-march-filter.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure></li></ul><a class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_button-prev swiper-button-prev swiper-button-white\" role=\"button\"></a><a class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_button-next swiper-button-next swiper-button-white\" role=\"button\"></a><a aria-label=\"Pause Slideshow\" class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_button-pause\" role=\"button\"></a><div class=\"wp-block-jetpack-slideshow_pagination swiper-pagination swiper-pagination-white\"></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Start and end states</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Compare the two images below</strong> showing the unmodified images versus the final dynamic, stylised profile images &#8211; all created by changing the URL! </p>\n\n\n\n<figure data-carousel-extra='{\"blog_id\":156412758,\"permalink\":\"https:\\/\\/datavis.blog\\/2023\\/01\\/23\\/tableau-image-role-and-cloudinary\\/\"}'  class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3406\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2023/01/23/tableau-image-role-and-cloudinary/02-image-no-edits/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"1000,711\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"02-image-no-edits\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=736\" data-id=\"3406\"  src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=1000\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3406\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/02-image-no-edits.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"3421\" data-permalink=\"https://datavis.blog/2023/01/23/tableau-image-role-and-cloudinary/08b-dynamic-jan/\" data-orig-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"1000,711\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"08b-dynamic-jan\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan.jpg?w=300\" data-large-file=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan.jpg?w=736\" data-id=\"3421\"  src=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan.jpg?w=1000\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3421\" srcset=\"https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan.jpg 1000w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan.jpg?w=150 150w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan.jpg?w=300 300w, https://datavisdotblog.files.wordpress.com/2023/01/08b-dynamic-jan.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>It’s unlikely you will want images to be the primary visual display for your data but they could make a nice compliment to existing charts and graphs in the right situation and I could definitely see some use cases for sports visualisations.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Video Tutorial</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>See the video below for a walkthrough of the dashboard used in the above examples and to see new images be dynamically generated based on parameter changes along with some other image options.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"736\" height=\"414\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Zwt6eDCA_YM?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-gb&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></div>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">More image role examples</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>More examples from the Tableau community:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://cj-mayes.com/2023/01/06/charting-the-nba-playoffs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Blog post</a> on using image roles with sports team logos from <a href=\"https://twitter.com/_CJMayes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">CJ Mayes</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://public.tableau.com/app/profile/lm.7/viz/WikipediaURL/EN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Workbook</a> with URLs for all country flags from <a href=\"https://twitter.com/LunarModule7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">LM-7</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://public.tableau.com/app/profile/brrosenau/viz/HexCodePreviewerXMLGenerator/HexCodePreviewerXMLGenerator\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Workbook</a> using image role in a colour palette generator from <a href=\"https://twitter.com/brrosenau\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Brittany Rosenau</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li>This <a href=\"https://workout-wednesday.com/2023w1tab/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">challenge</a> from the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/WorkoutWednsday\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WorkoutWednesday</a> team</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Video <a href=\"https://youtu.be/fSRzNi-_u5g\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">one</a> and <a href=\"https://youtu.be/37xBp2BCQgw\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">two</a> from <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TableauTim\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Tim Ngwena</a> on Cloudinary and image roles</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Thanks for reading!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Marc</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-social-links has-icon-color has-icon-background-color is-style-default is-content-justification-left is-layout-flex wp-container-3\"><li style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000; \" class=\"wp-social-link wp-social-link-twitter wp-block-social-link\"><a rel=\" noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/datavisblog\" class=\"wp-block-social-link-anchor\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.1\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\"><path d=\"M22.23,5.924c-0.736,0.326-1.527,0.547-2.357,0.646c0.847-0.508,1.498-1.312,1.804-2.27 c-0.793,0.47-1.671,0.812-2.606,0.996C18.324,4.498,17.257,4,16.077,4c-2.266,0-4.103,1.837-4.103,4.103 c0,0.322,0.036,0.635,0.106,0.935C8.67,8.867,5.647,7.234,3.623,4.751C3.27,5.357,3.067,6.062,3.067,6.814 c0,1.424,0.724,2.679,1.825,3.415c-0